West Dean is set in the valley of the [[River Lavant, West Sussex|River Lavant]] in the [[South Downs]] has an [[Anglican]] parish church dedicated to Saint Andrew. The church and most of the houses are built of [[flint]], usually with brick [[Quoin (architecture)|quoins]] and window dressings. There is one pub, the'' Selsey Arms''.
==West Dean House==

The village is dominated by [[West Dean House]], a large mansion built of flint which now houses [[West Dean College]], an arts and crafts school.<ref>[http://www.westdean.org.uk/ West Dean College]</ref> The house, built by the Peachey family in 1804, was later bought by the James family and was the home of [[Edward James]], who donated it to a charitable trust in 1964. The gardens around the house are open to the public and have well preserved Victorian walled gardens and glasshouses. There is also a park and [[arboretum]].<ref>[http://www.westdean.org.uk/site/gardens/ West Dean Gardens]</ref>
